{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any question we should add: "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"mailto:info@zeezide.de"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Object-Relational-Mappers-ORM","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Object Relational Mappers (ORM)"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Relationship to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Object–relational_mapping"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"What-is-different-to-an-ORM","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"What is different to an ORM?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Object"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Relational Mapper usually maintains a graph of interconnected"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects (as objects, reference types)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lighter doesn’t do any objects, the Lighter generated model types are structures"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that directly map to the SQLite tables and views, in a typesafe manner."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While it can also generate fetchers for relationships,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it doesn’t represent such within the models."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example a Northwind "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Order"},{"type":"text","text":" model doesn’t have an associated "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"product"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference property"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(Lighter "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"does"}]},{"type":"text","text":" generate the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"db.products.fetch(for: order)"},{"type":"text","text":" fetch function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"though)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lighter also doesn’t do any caching or invalidation, i.e. no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“managed object context”. Lighter record structures are context free (i.e. also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"do not refer to the database in any way)."}]},{"anchor":"Is-Lighter-a-replacement-for-CoreData","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Is Lighter a replacement for CoreData?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can be, but it is a lot lower level than CoreData. Which can be an advantage,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"especially for performance. It also keeps things simple, less surprises."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CoreData is a rich framework that goes as far as providing direct SwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integration."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Lighter doesn’t do anything like that "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"intentionally"}]},{"type":"text","text":". It is supposed to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lighter"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(Stay tuned for Heavier™️.)"}]},{"anchor":"Is-Lighter-a-replacement-for-ZeeQL","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Is Lighter a replacement for ZeeQL?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/zeeql.io"},{"type":"text","text":" situation is similar to CoreData."}]},{"anchor":"SQLite-Access-Libraries","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"SQLite Access Libraries"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A set of SQLite Swift libraries are already available."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The most popular one is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/groue\/GRDB.swift"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"another is SQLite.swift. ORMs like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ZeeQL also provide low level SQLite access."}]},{"anchor":"What-are-advantages-over-SQLiteswift-or-GRDB","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"What are advantages over SQLite.swift or GRDB?"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lighter has two main advantages over “regular” libraries:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It pre-generates fully typesafe (down to the SQL schema) structures for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all tables, one doesn’t have to type out the structures manually."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It pre-generates common queries in highly efficient code, avoiding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a lot of runtime “mapping overhead” and a lot of temporary allocations."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both libraries provide "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"type":"text","text":" support that can somewhat mirror the generated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"structures (i.e. provide more convenience)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"We found Codable to be extraordinarily slow (e.g. >19× slower when using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SQLite.swift)."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Performance"}]}]}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/lighter\/faq"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/FAQ","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A collection of questions and possible answers."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Frequently Asked Questions","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Lighter.swift for SQLite3"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Support","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Who","doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Troubleshooting"],"generated":true}],"references":{"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object–relational_mapping":{"title":"ORMs","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ORMs"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Object–relational_mapping","url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Object–relational_mapping"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter/Who":{"role":"article","title":"Support","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Built by @helje5."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter\/Who","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter\/who"},"https://zeeql.io":{"title":"ZeeQL","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ZeeQL"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/zeeql.io","url":"https:\/\/zeeql.io"},"doc://Lighter/documentation/Lighter":{"role":"collection","title":"Lighter.swift for SQLite3","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Type-safe down to the schema. Very, "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"very"}]},{"type":"text","text":", fast. Dependency free."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Lighter\/documentation\/Lighter","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/lighter"},"https://github.com/groue/GRDB.swift":{"title":"GRDB.swift","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GRDB.swift"}],"typ